name: New Adventures in Time and Space!
Enlightenment

description:
Heroic Publishing's demonic temptress, DARK MALICE, takes the spotlight in the first issue of this spanking-new comic book series designed to put the spotlight on new artists, concepts, and characters from the universe of Heroic Publishing.

In this first issue, writer F. P. Barbieri and artist Franco Urru delve into the mysteries of the dark goddess who brought about the destruction of Olympus and challenged a world!

Also in this issue, David Berge's demon-possessed martial artist INDIGO lives again, in the original special six-page preview by writer Dennis Mallonee and artists Rick Hoberg and Tim Burgard.Â
name: Malice's Story; Who Is Indigo?; Vittoria's Story

name: The Android Inavsion

description: Includes Part Two of the comic strip Pureblood.
name: Resurrection of The Daleks

name: The Two Doctors

name: The Celestial Toymaker

name: Image of The Fendahl

description: Includes Part Two of Paul Cornell's comic strip Emperor of the Daleks.
name: Time and The Rani

description: When 19th Century justice catches up with the infamous grave robbers Grimes and Blake, the condemned Blake reveals to the peculiar clergyman, Father Duffy, who you can never, ever trust a corpse. From GLENN McQUAID's award winning motion picture starring DOMINIC MONAGHAN, LARRY FASSENDEN and RON PERLMAN.Â

Â In 1996, "Legends of the Dead Earth" is a crossover event through all of the DC Annual's in that year.Â  The Earth and it's heroes have long since gone, however, those earthly legends live on throughout the universe and have been scattered over a thousand different worlds.Â  This is the story of Superman: The Man of Steel known as Kaleb, the last survivor of Hydros, his neverending battle alongside the Rebellion against the Empire headed by an ancient arch nemesis.
name: The Neverending Battle

volume.name: Superman: The Man of Steel Annual

description: A special extra-sized issue featuring a back-up tale by Pulitzer Prize-winning writer Michael Chabon The Amazing Adventures of Kavalier and Klay)! In the lead story, the modern day Mr. Terrific finds himself under surveillance by D.E.O. Agents. Wanting to get to the bottom of it, Mr. Terrific confronts Director Bones and discovers a few things that will challenge the smartest man alive and shake him to the very core of his soul! Plus, Michael Chabon and Michael Lark (GOTHAM CENTRAL) weave a 16-page tale revolving around the Golden Age Mr. Terrific and his troublesome brother.
name: Fair Enough

description: The character-centered mini-series comes to a heartfelt conclusion! At last, Justice Society regroups after confronting people and events of the past! But what was the true purpose of these visits? And how will the JSA stop a power they can't control? Guest-starring the Spectre!
name: And Justice For All

description: Kinsey and Bode find themselves in a desperate, seemingly unwinnable battle against a rising army of living shadows, while Tyler faces down Dodge in a terrifying duel of wits and wills.
name: Chapter Four: Shadow Play

description:
A third of the way into his remarkable run, Peter David introduced one of his most influential contributions to the Hulk's career: the Pantheon! David's dynamic demigods hit the scene just as the Hulk's finally getting his head together, no matter how many personalities are inside it! It's a circus in there, and what's a circus without...a Ringmaster? Plus: a Skrull invasion (yes, another one); Christmas with the Rhino; and the short, tragic career of Crazy Eight! Guest-starring Doc Samson and Nick Fury!

Collects Incredible Hulk Vol.2 #373-382.
name: Volume 6

description:
The Hulk continues his pulsating partnership with the Pantheon, and he'll need all the supporting characters he can get when half the universe disappears! Thanos has taken up the Infinity Gauntlet, but the Hulk instead suspects his endurable adversary Abomination - and it should be easy to investigate from the ground up...when he's shrunken to six inches tall! Plus: hard choices, harder punches and the death of a longtime Hulk ally. Guest-starring Doctor Strange, the Man-Thing and Sabra the Super-Agent!

Collects Incredible Hulk Vol.2 #383-389 and Incredible Hulk Vol.2 Annual #17 (select material).
name: Volume Seven

description:
It didnât matter very much what you gave Ken Bradley, boxer turned paratrooper, to fight with. His bare fists made him a match for a handful of Germans any day.
But give him a gun, especially a Tommy gun, and heâd take on anything that had a swastika painted on it. Even a tankâ¦or a pill-box! What a man to have a your side.
name: Battling Bradley

description: Cadet pilot Willi Ferman had only one ambition - to fly a Luftwaffe fighter. But, as the Second World War neared its end, the German Army was so short of men to stop the Russian advance that Willi and his fellow cadets were posted to the infantry, rifles thrust into their hands.Yet, through all the terrors of trying to stop the vengeful Russians, Willi kept his dream alive of being a fighter pilot... even though all the odds were stacked against him.
name: "Let Me Fly!"

description: After all but dying in the Crimean War, Cavalryman Henry Ball decided he'd had a bellyful of war. He sailed for the US intending to make a new life, as far from anything military as he could manage.At first his life went well and he prospered as a farmer. Unfortunately for him, though, the states of North America were soon at war with one another. How long could he avoid being drawn into their civil war?
name: Second Chance for Glory

description: With the Korean War over, the men of Ramsey's Raiders were wondering if they were bound for Civvy Street once more. They needn't have worried. The Army soon found another mission for them, but it would be totally different to anything these veterans of irregular warfare were used to.The team was soon posted to Malaya to fight a mysterious, shadowy enemy. However, after intensive training, the Raiders were ready for the dangers of the humid, claustrophobic jungle...weren't they?
name: Raiders at the Ready

description: It seemed a simple enough job for an experienced Mountie - help the Army track down some escaped German prisoners and get them back to their Canadian POW cage.But these were no ordinary prisoners. Highly-trained and highly-skilled, they ran rings round their pursuers. The question was, would Mountie Ross MacDonald give them up or could he force them into a mountain showdown?
name: Mountain Showdown

description: They say you can't pick up military tactics from a book - learning in the field is the only way. But fledgling tank commander Second-Lieutenant Jeff Hammond, desperate to evade pursuing German panzers in the desert, had no experience and only a textbook to help him. And his survival manual wasn't some dusty old tome - it was a paperback Western novel!
name: Operation Apache

description: It was bad enough perishing in battle against the Luftwaffe in the cockpit of your Hurricane. It was something else to be murdered in the dark by someone who pretended to be a friend. And that's exactly what began to happen to a bunch of RAF pilots in France in the early days of the war...When death struck from the shadows!
name: Death from the Shadows

description: "My honour is true," was the proud boast of Hitler's SS.Members even had it engraved on the blades of their ceremonial daggers - daggers that were supposed never to be put back in their sheaths except with honour.Yet the SS fanatics took few prisoners in battle and the dagger became many a poor wretch's passport to doom...
name: Dagger of Doom

description: During the American Civil War, the fearless Captain William Bailey and his men struck terror into the hearts of the enemies with their daredevil raids behind the lines.Eighty years later it was the dream of tank Lieutenant Bill Bailey to lead another gang of raiders into action and gain the same glory as his famous ancestor. But he hadn't reckoned on a political conspiracy designed to keep him and his tank as far from the fighting as possible...
name: Bailey's Raiders

description: Twisting, diving weaving... it seemed there was nothing Helmut Starr could do to shake the Russian ace from his tail - this Red Air Force legend who had already sent many a German pilot to an early grave.Then Helmut's Messerschmitt shuddered violently, black smoke gushing from the engine. Russian rounds had found their target, and were sending him spinning earthwards. Was this the end of Starr's war?
name: Starr's War

description: In the Khyber Pass, a patrol of British soldiers being ambushed was not unusual. What was unusual were the modern weapons being used by the ambushers.All the evidence pointed to a gun runner supplying the local tribes. And it would fall to a young British officer to track him down before his actions started a full-scale war.For George Harrington it would be a baptism of fire.
name: Gun Runner

description: Captain Jimmy Ramsey's crack squad of raiders are getting plenty of action rescuing downed pilots during the Korean War. Even so, they wouldn't mind a bit more of a challenge...When that comes in the form of a dangerous mission to take out a Chinese MiG base, they are raring to go. Then they learn that they must team up with a French Foreign Legion group, some of whom previously served in Hitler's Armies.Working alongside their deadliest foes from the last war could prove to be the biggest challenge of all!
name: Raiders on the Rampage

description: Africa, 1915, and Lieutenant Archie Draper is the lone survivor of an unexplained incident that claims the lives of all his fellow soldiers and their German prisoners.Over twenty years later, during World War II, Archie is still determined to solve once and for all the mystery of the deadly, though seemingly harmless, valley in the Cameroun highlands. And he has some help - in the form of the amazing Eagle airship and her crew.He'll need that help too, for they have to deal with a ruthless Italian death squad out to make history repeat itself...
name: Eagle of Africa

description: Luck charms, every soldier has one or has a mate who has one. And everyone knows they don't work. Not a single one of them.Billy Selby was convinced his was different, though. His had saved his granddad in the First World War and now it would save him. Wouldn't it?
name: Bullet-proof Billy

description: Tony Riley was born to fly. Both his father and his uncle had been pilots in the First World War, so it was only natural that Tony should want to be a pilot in 1939.But not even that heritage or all the training or his ability was to prepare Tony for what lay ahead - the feeling that a ghost was flying by his side in the cockpit...
name: Ghost in the Cockpit

description: Skill with a rifle is only part of the sniper's trade. Just as important are nerves of steel and endless patience.Crack-shot Bill Gibson had all three - he also had a powerful hunting rifle and the perfect position from which to fire the bullet that could change the course of history...
name: Lone Sniper

description: Although he was a descendant of Joshia Penn, the bloodthirsty pirate, Henry Penn was not a fighting man. Then the peace of his South Sea Island paradise was shattered by a U-Boat attack and even Henry realised that it was time to go to war.Armed with a rifle and an ancient cannon, Henry took on the German Navy - using a few tricks that would have delighted old Joshia!
name: Pirates on Parade

description: April, 1982 - Argentine troops poured on to the Falkland Islands and Britain stood on the brink of war. For Gary Mullen of the elite Special Boat Squadron it meant at last the chance to put the deadly skills acquired over years of training to the ultimate test!
name: The Deadly trade

description: General Marcel Moran was an inspiration to his fellow Frenchmen. Brave, intelligent and resourceful, he led from the front, never expecting his soldiers to do anything that he wouldn't do himself.For all these reasons and more, the Germans knew that Moran had to be dealt with. But killing the charismatic leader would turn him into a martyr so the S.S. hatched other plans...
name: Lead from the Front!

description: THEY'RE BACK!After completing daring and dangerous missions from North Africa to Germany during World War II, the men of the Special Raiding Force retired in 1945. Civilian life did not sit well with them, however, and especially not with the unit's tough leader, Scotsman Captain Jimmy Ramsey.So, when the Korean War exploded in 1950 and they were recalled by the top brass, Jimmy Ramsey jumped at this final chance to see some more action. And his team jumped too.However, this conflict would prove to be more dangerous than anything Ramsey's Raiders had experienced before...
name: Raiders Recalled

description:
A group of German raiders were destroying British supply dumps in the North African desert. They seemed to appear from nowhere then disappear into the night sky like shadows when their deadly work was done.

British Intelligence suspected that the enemy were using Zeppelins to escape. But those flying hulks were obsolete. Weren't they?

Try telling that to the men charged with stopping the marauding Jerries - the crew of the most amazing airship of them all... the Fighting Eagle.
name: The Fighting Eagle

description: âStand by for a crash â young Danny Price has just taken off!â What a reputation for a young pilot to get. Too bad that every word of it was true. From recklessness and bad judgement, or maybe just through bad luck, Dan finished up pranging every aircraft he ever flew. Spitfires, Hurricanes, Grumman Wildcats â they were all the same to Dan. In the sea, in the fields, on the decks of carriers he dumped them with amazing regularity, totally beyond repair. Not until he crashed one with cold courage right on to an attacking U-Boat did anyone start believing in Dan â even Dan himself!
name: Lone Ace
Death Cloud

description:
They flew their scrapheaps into some mighty strange places

Donald Ducks, Flying Scrapheaps, Rattletraps. Walrus crews got fed up of the names other blokes called their big clumsy Walrus flying-boats.
Then an RAF desert bomber group asked for fighter support and, to their horror, in lumbered two air-sea rescue Walruses!
Not until their own bombers were destroyed the day before a big raid did the RAF scoffers find out what those ârattle-trapsâ could do in the hands of pilots like Bill Donovan and Al Tucker.
Then âDonovanâs Ducksâ took off in a blaze of glory.
name: Walrus Patrol

description: The story of William "Braveheart" Wallace
name: The Scottish Chiefs

description:
By 1945, the Allied vice was closing in on the doomed Third Reich. Though some diehards, convinced of a final Nazi victory, were fighting on, most Allied soldiers were thinking about going home when the fighting was done.

For one group of British soldiers on Germany's northern coast those hopes would be shattered. And, though war-weary, the British were still full of fight. But what could they do against an aggressor they couldn't even see!
name: Invisible Aggressor

description: The Teen Titans join forces with The Titans and The Vigilante in this new title collecting the "Deathtrap" storyline from TEEN TITANS ANNUAL 2009, TITANS #12 and 13, TEEN TITANS #70 and VIGILANTE #5 and 6.
name: Deathtrap
